Checklist before Day 7 (integration testing & polish)


 Submitting a review for a non-DELIVERED order is rejected; works once the order is DELIVERED

 A second review attempt on the same order is rejected with DuplicateResourceException

 After a review is submitted, restaurants.avg_rating actually changes — verify by calling Restaurant Service directly

 Killing Restaurant Service and submitting a review still succeeds (best-effort average push, matching the Notification pattern from Day 5)

 Admin approving a restaurant actually flips its approval_status in Restaurant Service, and produces one new row in audit_logs

 Admin disabling a user actually flips is_active in Auth Service, and produces one new row in audit_logs

 Every one of the 9 business services registers with Eureka and shows a green status

 Every service's Swagger UI (/swagger-ui.html) loads and lists both public and internal endpoints


All 9 business services + 3 infrastructure services are now built. Day 7 shifts from "generate new code" to: running the full end-to-end flow (register → browse → cart → checkout → payment → delivery → review → admin oversight) through the API Gateway, fixing whatever breaks at the seams between services, and tidying up README/Swagger descriptions. Want that Day 7 checklist/guide next, or do you want to build through Day 6 first?

